  "Idea": "We propose a novel framework, 'Self-Reconditioning Attention via Meta-Stable Skeleton Decomposition' (SRAS), which fundamentally rethinks how skeleton decomposition can be stabilized in self-attention approximation. Rather than treating numerical instability as an unavoidable consequence of low-rank approximation to be mitigated heuristically, SRAS introduces a learnable, input-adaptive preconditioning mechanism that proactively shapes the attention matrix into a form inherently resistant to ill-conditioning during decomposition. At the core of SRAS is a lightweight meta-network that predicts a diagonal preconditioning matrix applied to the query and key projections based on real-time estimates of attention entropy and gradient sensitivity. This meta-preconditioner dynamically rescales feature dimensions to equalize their contribution to the attention logits, thereby promoting well-distributed singular values in arbitrary skeleton submatrices. Crucially, this process is differentiable and trained end-to-end using a stability-aware objective that minimizes both task loss and a spectral flatness penalty over sampled intersection matrices. To further enhance robustness, SRAS incorporates two new regularization components: (1) Confidence-Weighted Implicit Regularization (CWIR), where the current softmax temperature is adjusted per token based on attention entropy—low entropy leads to stronger anchoring to the full-rank attention prior, preventing divergence; and (2) Inter-Skeleton Consistency Regularization (ICR), which enforces output equivalence between multiple stochastically sampled skeleton decompositions of the same attention block, promoting invariant reconstruction regardless of selection path. This dual regularization ensures that the model does not overfit to a particular skeleton configuration and instead learns a stable, canonical low-rank manifold. The significance of SRAS lies in its ability to enable reliable self-attention approximation at extremely low ranks (e.g., r=32) without degradation in performance or training instability. By making the representation itself numerically robust, rather than just selecting safer components, SRAS opens the door to scalable, trustworthy sparse attention for trillion-token sequences in language, video, and multimodal modeling. Potential impact includes reduced memory footprint, improved training dynamics, enhanced adversarial robustness due to smoother loss landscapes, and broader applicability of skeleton methods beyond Transformers to other factorization-heavy architectures.",
